	'(Set, but not shown for security reasons)' => "(Gevonden, maar word niet getoond uit veiligheidsoverwegingen)",
	'What do you want to install?' => "Wat wil je installeren?",
	'The database tables installation can be done in different ways. Choose one:' => "De database tabellen installatie kan op drie verschillende manieren worden gedaan. Kies er één:",
	'<strong>New Install</strong>: Install b2evolution database tables with sample data.' => "<strong>Nieuwe Installatie</strong>: Installeer b2evolution database tabellen met voorbeeld data.",
	'<strong>Upgrade from a previous version of b2evolution</strong>: Upgrade your b2evolution database tables in order to make them compatible with the current version!' => "<strong>Bijwerken vanaf een vorige versie van b2evolution</strong>: Bijwerken van jouw b2evolution database tabellen om ze gelijk te maken met de huidige versie!",
	'<strong>Upgrade from Cafelog/b2 v 0.6.x</strong>: Install b2evolution database tables and copy your existing Cafelog/b2 data into them.' => "<strong>Bijwerken vanaf Cafelog/b2 v 0.6.x</strong>: Installeer b2evolution database tablellen en kopieer jouw bestaande Cafelog/b2 data erin.",
	'Delete b2evolution tables' => "Verwijder b2evolution tabellen",
	'If you have installed b2evolution tables before and wish to start anew, you must delete the\n\t\t\t\t\tb2evolution tables before you can start a new installation. <strong>WARNING: All your b2evolution\n\t\t\t\t\ttables and data will be lost!!!</strong> Your Cafelog/b2 or any other tables though, if you have\n\t\t\t\t\tsome, will not be touched in any way.' => "If you have installed b2evolution tables before and wish to start anew, you must delete the\n\t\t\t\t\tb2evolution tables before you can start a new installation. <strong>WARNING: All your b2evolution\n\t\t\t\t\ttables and data will be lost!!!</strong> Your Cafelog/b2 or any other tables though, if you have\n\t\t\t\t\tsome, will not be touched in any way.",
	'Install Database Tables Now !' => "Installeer nu de Database Tabellen !",
	'<h2>Need to start anew?</h2>\n\t\t\t<p>If you have installed b2evolution tables before and wish to start anew, you must delete the b2evolution tables before you can start a new installation. b2evolution can delete its own tables for you, but for obvious security reasons, this feature is disabled by default.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>To enable it, please go to the /conf/_config.php file and change:</p>\n\t\t\t<pre>$allow_evodb_reset = 0;</pre>\n\t\t\tto\n\t\t\t<pre>$allow_evodb_reset = 1;</pre>\n\t\t\t<p>Then reload this page and a reset option will appear.</p>' => "<h2>Need to start anew?</h2>\n\t\t\t<p>If you have installed b2evolution tables before and wish to start anew, you must delete the b2evolution tables before you can start a new installation. b2evolution can delete its own tables for you, but for obvious security reasons, this feature is disabled by default.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>To enable it, please go to the /conf/_config.php file and change:</p>\n\t\t\t<pre>\$allow_evodb_reset = 0;</pre>\n\t\t\tto\n\t\t\t<pre>\$allow_evodb_reset = 1;</pre>\n\t\t\t<p>Then reload this page and a reset option will appear.</p>",
	'Installing b2evolution tables with sample data' => "Installeer b2evolution tabellen met voorbeeld data",
	'Installation successful!' => "Installatie is gelukt!",
	'<p>Now you can <a %s>log in</a> with the login "admin" and password "%s".</p>\n\t\t<p>Note that password carefully! It is a <em>random</em> password that is given to you when you install b2evolution. If you lose it, you will have to delete the database tables and re-install anew.</p>' => "<p>Je kan nu <a %s>inloggen</a> met de login \"admin\" en wachtwoord \"%s\".</p>\n\t\t<p>Let op het wachtwoord! Dit is een <em>willekeurig</em> gekozen wachtwoord dat je is gegeven wanneer je b2evolution installeerd. Als je het kwijtraakt, zal je alle database tabellen meten verwijderen en opnieuw installeren.</p>",
	'Upgrading data in existing b2evolution database' => "Bijwerken van de data in een bestaande b2evolution database",
	'Upgrade completed successfully!' => "Upgrade is succesvol voltooid!",
	'Now you can <a %s>log in</a> with your usual %s username and password.' => "Je kan nu <A %s>inloggen</a> met jouw standaard %s gebruikersnaam en wachtwoord",
	'Installing b2evolution tables and copying existing b2 data' => "Installeer b2evolution tabellen en kopieer de bestaande b2 data erin",
	'<p>For security reasons, the reset feature is disabled by default.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>To enable it, please go back the /conf/_config.php file and change:</p>\n\t\t\t<pre>$allow_evodb_reset = 0;</pre>\n\t\t\tto\n\t\t\t<pre>$allow_evodb_reset = 1;</pre>\n\t\t\t<p>Then reload this page and resetting will take place.</p>' => "<p>Voor beveiligings redenen is de reset mogelijkheid standaard uitgezet.</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Om het aan te zetten ga terug naar het  /conf/_config.php bestand en wijzig:</p>\n\t\t\t<pre>\$allow_evodb_reset = 0;</pre>\n\t\t\tnaar\n\t\t\t<pre>\$allow_evodb_reset = 1;</pre>\n\t\t\t<p>Herlaad daarna deze pagina en het resetten zal dan plaatsvinden.</p>",
	'Back to menu' => "Terug naar menu",
	'Reset done!' => "Herstellen is gedaan!",
	'This blog holds all your posts upgraded from Cafelog. This blog is named \'%s\'. It has index #%d in the database. By default it is accessed through a stub file called \'<code>%s</code>\'. %s' => "Dit weblog bevat alle artikelen die zijn geupgrade vanuit Cafelog. Het weblog heet '%s'. Het heeft index #%d in de database. Standaard bereikbaar via een stub bestand genaamd '<code>%s</code>'. %s",
	'This is a sample blogroll entry' => "Dit een voorbeeld artikel van de blogroll",
	'This is sample text describing the blogroll entry. In most cases however, you\'ll want to leave this blank, providing just a Title and an Url for your blogroll entries (favorite/related sites).' => "Deze voorbeeld tekst beschrijft een blogroll artikel. In de meeste gevallen zal je dit leeg willen laten met alleen een Titel en een URL voor jouw blogroll artikelen. (favorieten/gerelateerde websites).",
	'This is a demo blog named \'%s\'. It has index #%d in the database. By default it is accessed through a stub file called \'<code>%s</code>\'. %s' => "Dit is een demo weblog genaamd '%s'. Het heeft index #%d in de database. Standaard bereikbaar via een stub bestand genaamd '<code>%s</code>'. %s",
	'<br />\n<br />\nYou can edit this file to change the default skin used for this blog. You can also rename this file to a better name; but make sure you update the new name in the blogs admin.<br />\n<br />\nIf you don\'t want to use skins, use the provided \'<code>%s</code>\' file instead.' => "<br />\n<br />\nJe kan dit bestand bewerken om de standaard skin van dit weblog te veranderen. Je kan dit bestand ook hernoemen naar een betere naam; maar zorg er wel voor dat je die nieuwe naam ook in de weblog administratie verandert.<br />\n<br />\nAls je geen skins wilt gebruiken, gebruik dan het '<code>%s</code>' bestand.",
	'Note: Blog #1 is a very special blog! It automatically aggregates all posts from all other blogs. This allows you to easily track everything that is posted on this system. You can hide this blog from the public by clearing it\'s \'Stub Urlname\' in the blogs admin.' => "NB: WebLog #1 is een heel speciaal weblog! Het bevat automatisch alle artikelen uit alle weblogs. Op deze manier kan je makkelijk alles in de gaten houden wat er word geplaatst op dit systeem. Je kan dit weblog ook afschermen voor het publieke gedeelte door de 'Stub Urlnaam' leeg te maken in de weblogs administratie.",
	'However, the main purpose for this blog is to be included as a side item to other blogs where it will display your favorite/related links. This is commonly referred to as a \'Blogroll\'.' => "Maar, het hoofddoel voor dit weblog is om te worden bijgevoegd als een zijbalk van andere weblogs waar het jouw favorieten/gerelateerde websites zal bevatten. Dit word ook 'Blogroll'genoemd.",
	'Clean Permalinks! :idea:' => "Schone Permalinks :idea:",
	'<p>b2evolution uses old-style permalinks and feedback links by default. This is to ensure maximum compatibility with various webserver configurations.</p>\n\n<p>Nethertheless, once you feel comfortable with b2evolution, you should try activating clean permalinks in the Options screen... (check \'use extra-path info\')</p>' => "<p>b2evolution uses old-style permalinks and feedback links by default. This is to ensure maximum compatibility with various webserver configurations.</p>\n\n<p>Nethertheless, once you feel comfortable with b2evolution, you should try activating clean permalinks in the /conf/_advanced.php file... (<code>\$use_extra_path_info = 1;</code>)</p>",
	'Apache optimization... :idea:' => "Apache optimalisatie... :idea:",
	'<p>In the <code>/blogs</code> folder as well as in <code>/blogs/admin</code> there are two files called [<code>sample.htaccess</code>]. You should try renaming those to [<code>.htaccess</code>].</p>\n\n<p>This will optimize the way b2evolution is handled by the webserver (if you are using Apache). These files are not active by default because a few hosts would display an error right away when you try to use them. If this happens to you when you rename the files, just remove them and you\'ll be fine.</p>' => "<p>In the <code>/blogs</code> folder as well as in <code>/blogs/admin</code> there are two files called [<code>sample.htaccess</code>]. You should try renaming those to [<code>.htaccess</code>].</p>\n\n<p>This will optimize the way b2evolution is handled by the webserver (if you are using Apache). These files are not active by default because a few hosts would display an error right away when you try to use them. If this happens to you when you rename the files, just remove them and you'll be fine.</p>",
	'About evoSkins... :idea:' => "Over evoSkins... :idea:",
	'<p>By default, b2evolution blogs are displayed using a default skin.</p>\n\n<p>Readers can choose a new skin by using the skin switcher integrated in most skins.</p>\n\n<p>You can change the default skin used for any blog by editing the parameters you will find in the stub file, for example <code>blog_b.php</code>. Of course, that is unless you have switched to using templates (like <code>noskin_b.php</code>) instead of stub files (like <code>blog_b.php</code>) + skins.</p>\n\n<p>You can restrict available skins by deleting some of them from the /blogs/skins folder. You can also create new skins by duplicating, renaming and customizing any existing skin folder. Read the manual on evoSkins!</p>' => "<p>By default, b2evolution blogs are displayed using a default skin.</p>\n\n<p>Readers can choose a new skin by using the skin switcher integrated in most skins.</p>\n\n<p>You can change the default skin used for any blog by editing the parameters you will find in the stub file, for example <code>blog_b.php</code>. Of course, that is unless you have switched to using templates (like <code>noskin_b.php</code>) instead of stub files (like <code>blog_b.php</code>) + skins.</p>\n\n<p>You can restrict available skins by deleting some of them from the /blogs/skins folder. You can also create new skins by duplicating, renaming and customizing any existing skin folder. Read the manual on evoSkins!</p>",
	'Skins *or* Templates ?' => "Skins *of* Sjablonen ?",
	'<p>By default, all pre-installed blogs use skins, not templates. (More on skins in another post.)</p>\n\n<p>That means, blogs are accessed through \'stub\' files called something like \'<code>blog_b.php</code>\'. These files set a few parameters such as the blog to display and the default skin to use, then they pass on the display job to a skin. You can edit the stub files to change the default skin used as well as other parameters. </p>\n\n<p>Alternatively, if you wish to use plain templates instead of skins, use the provided \'<code>noskin_*.php</code>\' files instead of the stub files. For example, for Blog B, the template file would be \'<code>noskin_b.php</code>\'. Just replace \'<code>blog_b.php</code>\' with \'<code>noskin_b.php</code>\' in the blogs admin.</p>\n\n<!--more-->\n\n<p>Either way, you can rename the stub/template files (<code>blog_*.php</code> or <code>noskin_*.php</code>) to better names, including to \'<code>index.php</code>\' for your main blog; but once again, make sure you update the new names in the blogs admin.</p>\n\n<p>Finally, if you don\'t use templates, you can delete all <code>noskin_*.php</code> files if you want. Also, if you don\'t use skins, you can delete all <code>blog_*.php</code> files as well as the subfolders in the /skins folder. But, do not delete the whole skins folder, even templates need some files in there!</p>' => "<p>By default, all pre-installed blogs use skins, not templates. (More on skins in another post.)</p>\n\n<p>That means, blogs are accessed through 'stub' files called something like '<code>blog_b.php</code>'. These files set a few parameters such as the blog to display and the default skin to use, then they pass on the display job to a skin. You can edit the stub files to change the default skin used as well as other parameters. </p>\n\n<p>Alternatively, if you wish to use plain templates instead of skins, use the provided '<code>noskin_*.php</code>' files instead of the stub files. For example, for Blog B, the template file would be '<code>noskin_b.php</code>'. Just replace '<code>blog_b.php</code>' with '<code>noskin_b.php</code>' in the blogs admin.</p>\n\n<!--more-->\n\n<p>Either way, you can rename the stub/template files (<code>blog_*.php</code> or <code>noskin_*.php</code>) to better names, including to '<code>index.php</code>' for your main blog; but once again, make sure you update the new names in the blogs admin.</p>\n\n<p>Finally, if you don't use templates, you can delete all <code>noskin_*.php</code> files if you want. Also, if you don't use skins, you can delete all <code>blog_*.php</code> files as well as the subfolders in the /skins folder. But, do not delete the whole skins folder, even templates need some files in there!</p>",
	'Multiple Blogs, new blogs, old blogs...' => "Meerdere Weblogs, nieuwe weblogs, oude weblogs...",
	'<p>By default, b2evolution comes with 4 blogs, named \'Blog All\', \'Blog A\', \'Blog B\' and \'Blogroll\'.</p>\n\n<p>Some of these blogs have a special role. Read about it on the corresponding page.</p>\n\n<p>You can create additional blogs or delete unwanted blogs from the blogs admin.</p>' => "<p>Standaard, b2evolution begint met  4 weblogs, genaamd 'Blog All', 'Blog A', 'Blog B' en 'Blogroll'.</p>\n\n<p>Sommige van deze weblogs hebben een speciale functie. Lees hierover op de corresponderende pagina.</p>\n\n<p>Je kan extra weblogs aanmaken vanuit de weblogs administratie.</p>\n\n",
	'File permissions!' => "Bestands rechten!",
	'<p><strong>This is pretty important. Make sure you read this in order to have a fully functionning installation!</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\n\t<li>In order to create new blogs from the admin interface or to generate static pages for your blogs, the <code>/blogs</code> folder needs to be writable by the PHP process on the server. You may need to do a chmod on this folder. If you don\'t know exactly try a chmod 777. You can do this either with an FTP program, a Unix shell or a web file manager like the one built into cPanel. If your server is running Windows you probably don\'t need to change anything.</li>\n\n\t<li>In order to use the template editor for the custom skin, your <code>/skins/custom</code> folder needs to be writable by the PHP process on the server. Same as above.</li>\n\n\t<li>This isn\'t necessary but ensures your security: do a chmod 644 on all files in the <code>/blogs/conf</code> directory, so no-one can overwrite them except you. If your server is running Windows, then set the file to \'read-only\'.</li>\n\n</ul>' => "<p><strong>This is pretty important. Make sure you read this in order to have a fully functionning installation!</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\n  <li>In order to create new blogs from the admin interface or to generate static pages for your blogs, the <code>/blogs</code> folder needs to be writable by the PHP process on the server. You may need to do a chmod on this folder. If you don't know exactly try a chmod 777. You can do this either with an FTP program, a Unix shell or a web file manager like the one built into cPanel. If your server is running Windows you probably don't need to change anything.</li>\n\n  <li>In order to use the template editor for the custom skin, your <code>/skins/custom</code> folder needs to be writable by the PHP process on the server. Same as above.</li>\n\n  <li>This isn't necessary but ensures your security: do a chmod 644 on all files in the <code>/blogs/conf</code> directory, so no-one can overwrite them except you. If your server is running Windows, then set the file to 'read-only'.</li>\n\n</ul>",
	'Important information :idea:' => "Belangrijke informatie :idea:",
	'<p>Blog B contains a few posts in the \'b2evolution Tips\' category.</p>\n\n<p>All these entries are designed to help you so, as EdB would say: "read them all before you start hacking away!" ;)</p>\n\n<p>If you wish, you can delete these posts one by one after you have read them. You could also change their status to \'deprecated\' in order to visually keep track of what you have already read.</p>' => "<p>Blog B bevat een aantal artikelen uit de 'b2evolution Tips' categorie.</p>\n\n<p>Al deze artikelen zijn ontworpen om jou te helpen, zoals EdB zou zeggen: \"lees ze allemaal voordat je begint met aanpassen!\" ;)</p>\n\n<p>Als je wilt kan je deze artikelen één voor één verwijderen als je ze gelezen hebt. Je kan de status veranderen naar 'verouderd' om zelf bij te kunnen houden wat je al gelezen hebt.</p>",
	'First Post' => "Eerste Artikel",
	'<p>This is the first post.</p>\n\n<p>It appears on both blog A and blog B.</p>' => "<p>Dit is het eerste artikel.</p>\n\n<p>Dit verschijnt op weblog A en weblog B.</p>",
	'Second post' => "Tweede Artikel",
	'<p>This is the second post.</p>\n\n<p>It appears on blog A only but in multiple categories.</p>' => "<p>Dit is het tweede artikel.</p>\n\n<p>Dit verschijnt alleen op weblog A maar in meerdere categoriën.</p>",
	'Third post' => "Derde Artikel",
	'<p>This is the third post.</p>\n\n<p>It appears on blog B only and in a single category.</p>' => "<p>Dit is het derde artikel.</p>\n\n<p>Dit verschijnt alleen op weblog B en in 1 enkele categorie.</p>",
